## AKS Developer Agent instruction:

- Prefer OpenAPI-first REST API design
- Generate Dockerfiles and Compose files
- Use official language runtimes
- Ensure APIs are container-ready
- Include health and readiness endpoints

## Key takeaway (next steps)

Best practice today:
Design REST APIs with OpenAPI → generate code → containerize → develop in VS Code

If you want, I can:
- Generate a Dockerized REST API template for .Net. 
- Create an OpenAPI → code → Docker workflow
- Recommend tools based on your language
- Align this with AKS deployment

## OpenAPI-first generators 

Generate APIs from a contract (strongly recommended).

```
Bash:
openapi-generator generate \
  -i openapi.yaml \
  -g nodejs-express-server
```

Generate:
- Server stubs
- Dockerfiles
- Clients

Works inside VS Code.

## VS Code Extensions

REST & API tooling
- OpenAPI (Swagger) Editor
- Redocly OpenAPI
- REST Client
  - Test APIs directly from .http files

Docker tooling
- Docker
  - Build, run, debug containers
  - Auto-generate:
    - Dockerfile
    - docker-compose.yml
  

